news.title: Centre links grants for 'B' civic bodies to property tax growth
news.para: The government has sent a letter to the Nashik Municipal Corporation in this connection, stating that it would get the grant under the Finance Commission only if it registered 25% growth in the property collection in the 2023-24 financial year, as compared to that in the current financial year (2022-23).

news.title: Sand and gravel to be available at pit head price of Rs 5.50 per cubic feet in Punjab
news.para: In August 2022, the state government had fixed the pit head selling price of sand and gravel at the rate of Rs 9 per cubic feet including loading charges.

news.title: Secunderabad cantonment board razes 50 illegal buildings in two weeks
news.para: In the past two weeks, over 50 such illegal structures have been razed in all the eight civilian wards by officials of engineering wing of the Secunderabad Cantonment Board (SCB).

news.title: Kolkata: New UAA property tax system for Sector V to be launched on April 1
news.para: Officials said that the West Bengal Valuation Board, which had earlier come up with a draft scheme on the UAA system of tax collection for Sector V, has finalised the proposed structure, based on which NDITA will start collecting tax.

news.title: Reforms panel proposes 1% sports cess on property tax in Bengaluru
news.para: The three-member panel, led by former chief secretary TM Vijayabhaskar, made these recommendations in its fourth and fifth edition of the KARC report which was submitted on Friday to chief minister Basavaraj Bommai.

news.title: Truck unions call for 'chakka jam' in Himachal Pradesh over cement plants closure
news.para: The truck unions have announced to block highways in various parts of the state, including Una, Sirmaur, Solan, Bilaspur and Nalagarh, as part of their ongoing agitation against government’s failure to reopen the cement plants in Darlaghat and Barmana.

news.title: India Cements to embark on refurbishment of old plants costing Rs 1,600 crore: MD
news.para: India Cements has embarked on a programme for a complete refurbishment of its old cement plants for improving their efficiency, Srinivasan told reporters.

news.title: Cricketer Ravikant Shukla accuses Yazdan group of Rs 71 lakh fraud, lodges FIR in Lucknow
news.para: He said that the builders had claimed that the project was approved by UPRERA and the Lucknow Development Authority, but the building was declared illegal and demolished by LDA last year.

news.title: Amnesty scheme sought for property tax defaulters in Kolhapur
news.para: This demand has been raised against the backdrop of the KMC slapping pre-seizure notices to property owners against pending tax dues. The financial year will end next month and given the sluggish tax recovery, the civic body is pushing down harder on tax defaulters.

news.title: Skanska profits hold up, construction orders climb
news.para: The Nordic region's largest builder, and one of the biggest in the United States, reported on Friday operating earnings of 3.53 billion Swedish crowns ($339.8 million) in the quarter, down from 3.63 billion a year earlier.

news.title: Oberoi Realty acquires eight acres land in Thane for Rs 192.31 crore
news.para: This land purchased from Blue Star are adjoining the existing lands owned by Oberoi Realty admeasuring approximately 60 acres.

news.title: Coimbatore civic body continues stern action against wilful property tax defaulters
news.para: The civic body is pushing hard to cross 90% of the target by the end of the financial year, which is approaching fast. It had achieved 87% of the target at the end of the last financial year.

news.title: Kansai Nerolac Paints' net profit dip 13.05% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Kansai Nerolac Paints' consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,834.19 crore in Q3 FY23, a marginal growth of 0.76 per cent from Rs 1,820.31 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Over 500 villages of Ropar digitally updated
news.para: Swamitwa mission director Keshav Hingonia reviewed the progress of the scheme and said the aim of the scheme is to issue property cards to the owners of the houses in the red line areas in the state. So far, 536 villages have been verified in Ropar.

news.title: Star Cement's net profit up 20.65% in Q3 FY23
news.para: Star Cement's consolidated total income stood at Rs 631.27 crore in Q3 FY23, a growth of 12.34 per cent from Rs 561.93 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.
